# Wavefront OBJ — unit cube, half-extent 0.5, centered at origin.
# §3.11 batch 9b.2 — replaces the procedural `kCubeVertices` /
# `kCubeIndices` arrays in `examples/vulkan_renderer/src/MeshLoader.cpp`
# at runtime. Demoes the rpg_demo's `parseObjFile` → `createMesh` →
# `setDefaultMesh` end-to-end OBJ→GPU upload path.
#
# 8 unique positions + 6 per-face normals + 6 quads (fan-split into
# 12 triangles → 36 corners after parsing). Each quad references one
# shared normal so flat shading is preserved.

# Positions (1-based OBJ indexing).
v -0.5 -0.5 -0.5
v  0.5 -0.5 -0.5
v  0.5  0.5 -0.5
v -0.5  0.5 -0.5
v -0.5 -0.5  0.5
v  0.5 -0.5  0.5
v  0.5  0.5  0.5
v -0.5  0.5  0.5

# Face normals (axis-aligned).
vn  0  0 -1
vn  0  0  1
vn  0 -1  0
vn  0  1  0
vn -1  0  0
vn  1  0  0

# Faces — winding is CCW as viewed from OUTSIDE each face (i.e. the
# right-hand-rule cross product of the first two triangle edges agrees
# with the declared face normal). With the opaque pipeline's
# frontFace=CCW + cullMode=BACK, this leaves outside faces visible and
# culls the inside walls.
#
# 2026-05-22 audit (round 8) — original asset had every quad wound in
# the reverse order, so the renderer culled the OUTSIDE of every cube
# and showed the inside walls instead ("open boxes" / "lighting less
# prominent" — regressed from commit 146b0be7 → f51ebf86 when this
# OBJ replaced the procedural kCubeVertices whose indices already
# encoded CCW-from-outside). Each quad was flipped from (a,b,c,d)
# to (a,d,c,b) to restore the convention.
f 1//1 4//1 3//1 2//1
f 5//2 6//2 7//2 8//2
f 1//3 2//3 6//3 5//3
f 4//4 8//4 7//4 3//4
f 1//5 5//5 8//5 4//5
f 2//6 3//6 7//6 6//6
